Sex trafficking of an individual under the age of 18. Second element. In considering whether Ms. Maxwell knew that Carolyn had not attained the age of 18, please apply the definition of "knowingly" previously provided to you. Instruction No. 28. Count Six. Sex trafficking of an individual under the age of 18. Third element. The third element of Count Six which the government must prove beyond a reasonable doubt is that Ms. Maxwell knew that the person Carolyn would be caused to engage in a commercial sex act. The term "commercial sex act" means any sex act on account of which anything of value is given to or received by any person.
